app.desc:
The PJRC Teensy 3.2 is a small, complete, and breadboard-friendly board based on the Freescale MK20DX256 32 bit ARM Cortex-M4.
developed in conjunction with the Arduino Company.

It has 24 5V tolerance digital input/output pins for breadboard use (of which 10 can be used as PWM outputs and 10 as analog inputs), a 72 MHz crystal oscillator (can be overclocked to 96MHz). It has a 256K Flash Memory, 64K RAM, 2K EEPROM.

In order to program the teensy through the Arduino IDE, all you have to do is to download & install the Teensyduino add-on..
